{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, in the domain of educational automation, the AugGPT framework leverages mutation scores as feedback signals to iteratively guide the LLM in generating test cases that uncover subtle errors in student code [172].",
    "Concurrently, differential testing provides a robust pseudo-oracle for behaviorally complex systems.",
    "TestGen [174] adopts this method by testing against multiple versions of JSON libraries.",
    "When an LLM-generated input results in inconsistent outputs, it is considered a valid test case; this approach successfully identified 34 real-world bugs in the fastjson2 library [174].",
    "For intricate logic, AID utilizes generator-based input construction and diversity-first differential testing to mitigate oracle errors [87].In addition, to ensure the co-evolution of test suites and software, LLMs are employed in test evolution tasks."
  ]
}